text: Maloustyinskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Maloustyinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 166 as of 2010. There are 9 streets. == Geography == It is located 5 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Maloustyinskoye
